-- CarMax earnings rise 15 percent
-- 
-- Thu Mar 29, 2007 11:01am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/29/us-carmax-results-idUSWEN587720070329

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - CarMax Inc. ( KMX.N ), the largest retailer of used cars in the United States, posted a 15 percent rise in quarterly earnings on Thursday, helped by strong sales and Internet traffic. 

 Earnings rose to $42.1 million, or 19 cents per share, in the fiscal fourth quarter ended February 28, from $36.7 million, or 17 cents per share, a year earlier. The latest results include an asset impairment charge of 1 cent per share related to a new car franchise. Analysts were expecting CarMax to earn 22 cents per share. Fourth-quarter sales rose 16 percent to $1.88 billion. CarMax forecast fiscal 2008 earnings of $1.03 to $1.14 per share. Analysts' average forecast is $1.08. The company said it plans to expand its used car stores by about 17 percent in fiscal 2008, opening 13 used car superstores. The company expects its capital expenditures to total $300 million in the year. CarMax said comparable-store sales of used cars are expected to grow 3 percent to 9 percent in fiscal 2008, and total revenue is expected to climb 14 percent to 20 percent.